# C - Pointers, Arrays, and Strings

## Description
This project covers the fundamentals of pointers, arrays, and strings in C. It helps in understanding how to work with memory addresses, manipulate data using pointers, and manage arrays and strings efficiently.

## Learning Objectives
- Understanding pointers and how they relate to arrays.
- Working with memory addresses and dereferencing.
- Manipulating strings and arrays using pointers.

## Files
- `file1.c`: Description of the task.
- `file2.c`: Description of the task.

## Requirements
- C compiler (GCC)
- Knowledge of basic C syntax
